      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Generally, an increase in the minimum wage can increase your operating costs significantly, which is a major concern for small businesses on tight budgets. To absorb these higher labor costs, you might need to adjust your pricing, which could impact your local customer base accustomed to low prices. Alternatively, you may need to look closely at streamlining operations or potentially reducing staffing hours. It's wise to forecast these potential changes to plan your financial strategy.",
